  <name>Stashee</name>
  <summary>Glass tiling terminal that stashes your workflows</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Terminals live in named workflows and tile themselves. Every pane
      runs inside tmux, so closing the app stashes a workflow instead of
      killing it — reopen, and every shell is back exactly where it was.
    </p>
    <p>
      Nothing to lose: quit, crash, update — sessions live in tmux, not
      in the app. SSH panes are stashed too, surviving reboots and
      dropped connections, and remote copy lands in the local clipboard.
      No settings GUI, no plugins, no daemons of its own — the app does
      very little, very well.
    </p>
  </description>
